    "last_updated": "2025-12-31",
    "excerpt": "This prayer, entitled \"[Prayer for] Our Enemies,\" was published in <em>The Jewish Peace Book for Home and School</em> (1932) under \"Section Ⅲ: Peace Devotions for Jewish Use — Prayers for Peace\" on pages 100-101. This prayer seems to me to be inspired by (or a reformulation of) the traditional twelfth blessing of the weekday Amidah, <span class=\"hebrew\">שׁוֹבֵר אוֹיְבִים וּמַכְנִיעַ זֵדִים</span> <em>shovér oyvim u-makhniya zedim</em> (\"who breaks enemies and overpowers evil ones\") a/k/a <em>la-malshinim</em> or <em>al haminim</em>. . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"/translate/\" target=\"_blank\">Contribute&nbsp;a&nbsp;translation</a></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nGrant, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Lord</span>,<br />\nthat we might overcome our enemies<br />\nby transforming them into friends.<br />\nMake them<br />\nand make us<br />\nconscious of those deep inward reaches<br />\nwhereby every heart is rooted<br />\nin the world’s deep common life.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nCause us<br />\nto cease looking into directions<br />\nthat oppose.<br />\nCause us, O thou <span class=\"divine-referent\">our Utmost Good</span>,<br />\nto look into the one direction<br />\nof a united look unto Thee.<br />\n<em>Amen</em>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This prayer, entitled &#8220;[Prayer for] Our Enemies,&#8221; was published in <em>The Jewish Peace Book for Home and School</em> (1932) under &#8220;Section Ⅲ: Peace Devotions for Jewish Use — Prayers for Peace&#8221; on pages 100-101. This prayer seems to me to be inspired by (or a reformulation of) the traditional twelfth blessing of the weekday Amidah, <span class=\"hebrew\">שׁוֹבֵר אוֹיְבִים וּמַכְנִיעַ זֵדִים</span> <em>shovér oyvim u-makhniya zedim</em> (&#8220;who breaks enemies and overpowers evil ones&#8221;) a/k/a <em>la-malshinim</em> or <em>al haminim</em>.